00:18:44,966 --> 00:18:46,700
<i>♪ Troy! Troy! Troy! Troy!</i>

472
00:18:47,301 --> 00:18:49,803
You know, bagpipes are sort of
anachronistic for this time...

473
00:18:49,805 --> 00:18:51,705
Quiet, you! Go back
to being vanquished.

474
00:18:51,707 --> 00:18:54,307
<i>♪ Troy! Troy! Troy! Troy!</i>

475
00:18:57,011 --> 00:18:58,078
(SCREAMING)

476
00:18:58,646 --> 00:19:00,413
♪ Troy! Troy! Troy! Troy!

477
00:19:05,153 --> 00:19:07,954
Troy! Troy! Troy! Troy.

478
00:19:08,156 --> 00:19:09,389
Oh, it's all over.

479
00:19:10,391 --> 00:19:13,393
♪ Doreen! Come out, come
out, wherever you are! ♪

480
00:19:13,395 --> 00:19:14,093
I should have...

481
00:19:14,095 --> 00:19:16,129
I should have brought some
bread crumbs or something

482
00:19:16,131 --> 00:19:17,898
to leave behind me
so I could find my way...

483
00:19:17,900 --> 00:19:20,433
Oh, you know what? Better yet, I
should have brought a sandwich,

484
00:19:20,435 --> 00:19:21,835
'cause I am famished.

485
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:26,839
(BEEPING)

486
00:19:28,809 --> 00:19:30,710
Hey, where you guys going?
We're not done yet.

487
00:19:30,712 --> 00:19:32,712
BOY 1: I gotta get home.
BOY 2: I've got book club.

488
00:19:32,714 --> 00:19:34,781
I've got
a balalaika lesson.

489
00:19:34,783 --> 00:19:36,750
You know, they've got a word
for what you guys are doing.

490
00:19:36,752 --> 00:19:38,852
Yeah. It's desertion.
No, it's...

491
00:19:38,854 --> 00:19:40,320
Oh, no.
It is desertion.

492
00:19:40,322 --> 00:19:41,688
Irving, get over here.

493
00:19:41,690 --> 00:19:43,790
It's time to execute Plan B.
Plan B?

494
00:19:43,792 --> 00:19:46,459
Yeah, you know the one where you
climb into the decoy and, uh...

495
00:19:46,461 --> 00:19:48,395
Oh, that Plan B.
Get going.

496
00:19:50,731 --> 00:19:52,299
A Trojan platypus?

497
00:19:52,301 --> 00:19:54,768
Come on, Buford, what makes
you think we'd fall for that.

498
00:19:54,770 --> 00:19:57,103
IRVING: I told you,
Buford. (YELLS)

499
00:19:57,105 --> 00:19:59,172
Why did you have me
get in this thing?

500
00:19:59,307 --> 00:20:00,874
Now, we're getting somewhere.

501
00:20:00,876 --> 00:20:03,476
Ha! I bet you didn't
see a Trojan T. rex

502
00:20:03,478 --> 00:20:06,446
with laser-cannon mouth and
laser eyes comin', did you?

503
00:20:06,781 --> 00:20:07,780
Well, he's got me there.

504
00:20:07,782 --> 00:20:10,784
Seriously, if you were just gonna
crush the Trojan platypus,

505
00:20:10,786 --> 00:20:12,719
why did I... Leave me
my simple pleasures.

506
00:20:12,721 --> 00:20:14,421
Now, Ferb,
destroy Troy!

507
00:20:14,423 --> 00:20:16,723
This is why I got
Ferb on my team!

508
00:20:16,725 --> 00:20:18,291
(GASPS)

509
00:20:20,161 --> 00:20:21,962
Uh-oh. Looks like
Ferb's goin' off book.

510
00:20:21,964 --> 00:20:23,129
Everyone to
the chariots!

511
00:20:23,831 --> 00:20:24,998
Hang on!

512
00:20:31,239 --> 00:20:34,040
Whoa-ho! Laser-proof.
Nice touch, Ferb.

513
00:20:35,509 --> 00:20:37,110
(YELLING)

514
00:20:37,511 --> 00:20:39,512
This is really cool.

515
00:20:40,514 --> 00:20:42,515
Book club starts
in 10 minutes.

516
00:20:43,417 --> 00:20:46,353
I have an idea! Throw that
rope to the other chariot!

517
00:20:49,257 --> 00:20:50,256
Well, that
can't be good.

518
00:20:50,258 --> 00:20:54,260
I guess they knew a T. rex's
weakness is also its Achilles' heel.

519
00:20:54,295 --> 00:20:55,528
(SCREAMING)

520
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:01,534
That was awesome!

521
00:21:01,869 --> 00:21:02,568
Who won?

522
00:21:02,570 --> 00:21:04,537
This time I think
it was a draw.

523
00:21:04,539 --> 00:21:06,506
Come on, let's go tell
Candace how it ends.

524
00:21:06,508 --> 00:21:08,074
Yeah, and maybe we
can pick up some

525
00:21:08,076 --> 00:21:09,809
Greek frozen
yogurt on the way.

526
00:21:11,112 --> 00:21:13,246
Doreen, come on,
quit kidding around.

527
00:21:13,248 --> 00:21:14,848
(GASPS)
Perry the Platypus?

528
00:21:14,850 --> 00:21:16,283
You've found the
De-clutterinator!

529
00:21:16,285 --> 00:21:17,550
Excellent,
okay, shoot me.

530
00:21:17,552 --> 00:21:19,486
Shoot me and I'll clean
this whole place up.

531
00:21:19,488 --> 00:21:20,286
Oh wait.
(STAMMERS) What?

532
00:21:20,288 --> 00:21:23,322
Oh, it's not plugged in.
Hold on one sec.

533
00:21:23,791 --> 00:21:25,225
My, word! What a mess.

534
00:21:25,793 --> 00:21:27,427
Okay, here's an open socket.

535
00:21:28,062 --> 00:21:29,396
That doesn't sound good.

536
00:21:29,398 --> 00:21:30,497
(EXPLOSION)

537
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:36,803
Oof, I say, I feel the
sudden urge to declutter.

538
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:41,975
Well, you have to admit it
did get rid of the clutter.

539
00:21:41,977 --> 00:21:43,209
There you are.

540
00:21:43,211 --> 00:21:44,844
Doreen!
What's happening?

541
00:21:44,846 --> 00:21:47,914
My invoice. You'll be
hearing from my lawyer.

542
00:21:48,049 --> 00:21:49,949
Curse you,
Perry the Platypus!

543
00:21:50,418 --> 00:21:53,286
And there goes
the last of it!

544
00:21:56,190 --> 00:21:58,458
Lawrence, what are
you doing out here?

545
00:21:58,460 --> 00:22:00,593
Oh, you know, just
tidying up a little.

546
00:22:00,595 --> 00:22:02,395
Well, the yard
looks great!

547
00:22:02,397 --> 00:22:03,395
Come on in the kitchen.

548
00:22:03,397 --> 00:22:05,298
I've got a plate of cake
that needs cleaning up.

549
00:22:05,300 --> 00:22:06,566
I'm your man.

550
00:22:10,004 --> 00:22:12,205
Now that we're all here.
Who wants to go first.

551
00:22:12,207 --> 00:22:14,974
Ooh, me! In general I thought
the Greeks' decoy platypus

552
00:22:14,976 --> 00:22:17,977
was a brilliant idea until it
got smashed by the T. rex!

553
00:22:17,979 --> 00:22:20,113
Its use of lasers to
destroy the city of Troy

554
00:22:20,115 --> 00:22:23,516
really seemed unbeatable until Paris
flew down in his laser chariot.

555
00:22:23,518 --> 00:22:26,119
The flying chariots were
all, pew, pew, pew, pew!

556
00:22:26,121 --> 00:22:27,354
Ga, ga, ga, ga!

557
00:22:27,356 --> 00:22:29,122
And... (IMITATES
BOMBS FALLING) Cool!

558
00:22:29,124 --> 00:22:30,924
<i>The Iliad </i> is truly an epic!

559
00:22:30,926 --> 00:22:33,493
Candace, you didn't
read the book, did you?

560
00:22:33,861 --> 00:22:34,560
I'm so busted.

561
00:22:34,562 --> 00:22:36,730
Oh, that's okay. I don't
think anyone did.

562
00:22:37,332 --> 00:22:38,865
I just come to book
club for the tea.

